 

App Name: google classroom 

Developer: google LLC 

Type of App:  A free educational and learning management platform 

Access Method:  browsers, mobile app, desktop, (iOS, windows, mac) 

Comments: 

A business communication platform is used for teachers to communicate with students, and students can be invited via a code specific to the class or automatically by the school, cloud-based platform integrated with workspace 

 

 

 

Does the app allow users to create a profile:  Yes 

Can profiles follow a workshop house style: Partly 

Comments: 

Teacher can create profiles with names and picture 

Users can have a linked to it from their company 

Users can not customize appearance because it is using standard layout 

 

Messaging: Yes 

Group chat/Channels: No 

Tutor announcements: Yes 

Audio/Video calls: Yes 

Comments: commutation support via comments and google meet. 

 

Different Web browser: Yes 

Desktop (Pc/Laptop): Yes 

Mobile: Yes 

Different operating system: Yes 

Comments: We can use Google Classroom on different browsers, devices, and even different operating systems, which makes it an easy-to-find and easy-to-use application. 

 

Secure login: Yes 

Role control (trainer/trainee): Yes 

Private groups: Yes 

Admin moderation: yes 

Comments: managed through google workspace admin 

 

Easy to Learn: Mostly 

Help & support available: Yes 

Key features (chat, Channel, files, calls) can be found without difficulty: Yes 

Navigation consistent across different sections of the app: Yes 

Users customize settings (notifications, theme, layout): Partly 

Comments:  

The interface is user-friendly, and users can access the (chat, file, calls) easily but it has a limit for the layout 

 

Accessible on different devices: Yes 

Supports inclusive learning (disabilities, or differences): Yes 

App offers captions or subtitles for audio/video content: Yes 

The app follows recognized accessibility standards (WCAG): Yes 

Comments:  

Google Classroom supports people with disabilities and facilitates access and learning, and supports mobile access, we don't have a direct video call but its support with google meet 

 

Does the app meet the workshop requirements: Partly 

Comments: Meets most requirements like multi-platform use and its suitable for blended and online learning except for a few restrictions applied to it.  

 

Advantage: Save Time, create work quickly, help students concentrate better, allow you to correct assignments, and return them to students directly through the app, can work on different platform 

Disadvantage: students may not have access to the same resources as online, has a Limits of Customizability, Notification maybe overwhelming, can be hard for beginners. 

Recommended for improvement: no limits on customization, increased security, and Finding Comfort in Distance Learning, provide guides for managing notification and accessibility. 

Comments: This improvement will enhance usability, more analytics, and reporting tools, easy for beginners 

 
